					<p class="sub-heading">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 21 DEVIATION CLAUSE. The Vessel shall have liberty to call at any ports in any order, to sail with or without pilots, to tow or to be towed, to go to the assistance of vessels in 
					distress, to deviate for the purpose of saving life or property or of landing any ill or injured person on board, and to call for fuel or stores at any port or ports in or out of the regular course of the voyage. Any salvage 
